{"name":"Last Stand","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Last Stand","type":"text","_id":"Y9Vl2eGRhUGAObFd","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>Sometimes, in a story of heroic proportions, a character simply falling unconscious due to physical stress is boring. Heroes defy the odds and get through insurmountable difficulties to complete their quest, even if it means staving off death for just a few more seconds. Last Stand actions allow you to do just that.</p><p>This variant rule introduces the Last Stand condition and trait. This condition is applied to any player character who has just been reduced to 0 hit points, before they fall unconscious. While in Last Stand, a character is prone, takes a -4 penalty to AC, can speak to an adjacent creature and can take one action at the start of their next turn, before rolling their first recovery check, after which they fall unconscious and become dying as normal. When a character gains the Last Stand condition, as usual for any creature reaching 0 hit points, they immediately move their initiative position accordingly. If a character with the Last Stand condition uses any action, reaction, or takes damage, they immediately fall unconscious and begin dying as normal. For any other purpose than the ability to take Last Stand actions, a character with the Last Stand condition is considered to be dying.</p><hr /><p>HANDLING LAST STAND AS A GM</p><p>Characters in Last Stand are often so wounded they could easily be confused with a dying or a dead character at first glance, and most intelligent creatures, unless extremely perceptive, would consider them out of the fight. When determining if you should strike a character during their Last Stand, consider the question the same way you would a dying character.</p><p>Alternatively, you can incorporate the slight distinction between Last Stand and Dying in the combat dynamic, by making an intelligent creature roll a perception check with a hard DC for its level when adjacent to a character in Last Stand, or by having the creature use the Seek action, like a wolf sniffing the body before deciding what to do next.</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":200000,"name":"Actions","type":"text","_id":"eJ81ruXx7iG6yYCR","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>Basic Actions</p><p>While in Last Stand, a character can only use three basic actions: Crawl, Seek, Recall Knowledge. When using the Seek or Recall knowledge action, the character can share the gathered information with the party as part of the action.</p><hr /><p>Class Actions</p><p>Every class treats its final moments differently. As such, each class has access to its own unique Last Stand action. Instead of using one of the listed basic actions, a character can spend a Hero Point to use its class specific Last Stand action.</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":300000,"name":"Class Actions","type":"text","_id":"HSzeGx6nOfLDFHIH","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>Alchemist</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.PVNbWMBqjcK8Hcu3]{Take This}</p><p>Barbarian</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.f5sgFUceCPBmEspJ]{Go Down Swinging}</p><p>Bard</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.Mo33UplIfabbysTW]{Dying Crescendo}</p><p>Champion</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.RUe23O7pos0DHJdG]{Final Defense}</p><p>Cleric</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.xfNyR6j9mpkWWewb]{Prayer of Protection}</p><p>Druid</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.oqUf7d7ZuwS5BP43]{Nature's Resilience}</p><p>Fighter</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.b4hVSYUp9TnIMLPI]{One Last Strike}</p><p>Gunslinger</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.5tkT2WcmfcgnWWby]{Pull the Trigger}</p><p>Inventor</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.vEkCtZNoJztAEMr8]{Last Resort}</p><p>Investigator</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.NU2Vye63MaJQGw16]{Hit Them There!}</p><p>Magus</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.wSg20VHa1okWn1q7]{Cascade Fallout}</p><p>Monk</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.v59dvlPEKEdZJCWs]{Meditation}</p><p>Ranger</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.wHczKVP2lQPLIeni]{Shared Edge}</p><p>Rogue</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.fU2fdAjvvE3fOhBx]{Not Dead Yet}</p><p>Sorcerer</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.KuOuRwijFyHVs92v]{Blood Panic}</p><p>Summoner</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.mqwpPLEFJ4WhswRl]{Exert Bond}</p><p>Swashbuckler</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.in5Hp4Gi3d4PNcrS]{One Last Trick}</p><p>Witch</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.Ly6OhDARIfiMsIVo]{Help Me Out}</p><p>Wizard</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.sinclairs-library-playtest.sinclairs-library-actions.hG4QA1OAFgvxzkIf]{Arcane Bolt}</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0,"XvAQTyKnzb1d2fbp":3},"flags":{"exportSource":{"world":"tabletop-obscura-presents-outlaws-of-alkenstar","system":"pf2e","coreVersion":"10.291","systemVersion":"4.6.4"},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.f9JyQq0EPCKwppzk"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4